{"article_id":"EbqRM1mq96voQuZf","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"The future of same-sex marriage and President Obama 's health care law hang in the balance","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"as the Supreme Court 's 2014 term draws rapidly to a close this month .","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"But those are n't the only big issues on the justices ' plate .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"Free speech and fair elections .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"Religious liberty and racial discrimination .","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"Clean air and capital punishment .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"All await rulings over the next three weeks","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"as the court completes action on 20 cases","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"remaining this term .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"The next decisions will come Thursday morning .","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"- Same-sex marriage .","depth":4},{"id":12,"text":"In a decision","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"likely to come on the term 's last day","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"- possibly June 29 or 30 -","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"the court will decide","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"whether gays and lesbians have a constitutional right","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"to marry","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"or whether state bans against same-sex marriage can remain in place .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"Six cases from Ohio , Michigan , Tennessee and Kentucky have been consolidated for the court 's consideration .","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"In them , 32 total plaintiffs are asking for the right","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"to marry","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"or to have marriages licensed elsewhere","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"recognized in their home states .","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"Most legal experts predict","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"the court ,","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"led by Justice Anthony Kennedy ,","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"will rule in favor of the gay and lesbian couples .","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"- Obamacare .","depth":5},{"id":29,"text":"The future of Obama 's health care law is on the line for the second time in three years ,","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"and it 's anyone 's guess how the court will rule .","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"Passed in 2010","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"and narrowly upheld by the court in a 5-4 ruling in 2012 ,","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"the law has extended health insurance to 12 million Americans .","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"But four words in its lengthy text","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"- `` established by the state '' -","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"now endanger federal subsidies","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"relied upon by 6.4 million participants in 34 states","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"that did not create their own exchanges or marketplaces .","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"The justices must decide","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"whether the law prohibits that financial aid .","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"- Clean air .","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"Environmental regulations","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"approved by the Obama administration","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"regularly come before the Supreme Court ,","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"and this year is no exception .","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"A major rule","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"requiring coal- and oil-fired power plants to reduce emissions of mercury and other toxic air pollutants","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"hangs in the balance .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"The justices appeared closely divided on the central issue in the case","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"- whether the Environmental Protection Agency should have considered the nearly $ 10 billion annual cost in relation to the potential benefits","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"before approving the regulation -","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"when it was argued .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"A decision in favor of objecting states and utilities could send the EPA back to the drawing board .","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"- Housing discrimination .","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"The third time could be the charm for the court 's conservatives ,","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"who tried twice in recent years to consider cases","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"challenging the way","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"housing bias claims are decided .","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"Under the Fair Housing Act of 1968 , minority groups have been able to win lawsuits","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"by showing","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"that housing practices","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"- such as sales , rentals , zoning and lending -","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"have a disparate impact on minorities .","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"Housing industry opponents","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"challenging the law","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"say","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"it was intended only to ban intentional discrimination .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"- Lethal injections .","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"The death penalty also is never far from the high court 's docket .","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"After a steady diet of cases and emergency appeals on issues such as claimed intellectual disabilities and the actions of defense lawyers and prosecutors , the court now must rule on a relatively new method of execution .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"The case involves the use of a sedative","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"called midazolam","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"as part of a three-drug cocktail","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"used by several states ,","depth":14},{"id":75,"text":"including Oklahoma ,","depth":15},{"id":76,"text":"where three death-row inmates are challenging its use .","depth":15},{"id":77,"text":"Unlike stronger barbiturates","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"that are in short supply ,","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"the drug has failed in some cases to block pain and suffering during the lethal injection process .","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"- License plates .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"This is a free speech case","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"that hinges on who is speaking","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"- the state government","depth":14},{"id":84,"text":"issuing specialty license plates","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"or the vehicles ' owners .","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"Texas ,","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"which like every other state issues such plates","depth":14},{"id":88,"text":"to produce revenue","depth":15},{"id":89,"text":"while promoting a variety of causes ,","depth":15},{"id":90,"text":"refused to approve the Sons of Confederate Veterans ' request for a plate","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"featuring the Confederate flag .","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"The justices must decide","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"if the government has the right","depth":14},{"id":94,"text":"to suppress its own speech","depth":14},{"id":95,"text":"or must allow private speech by motorists ,","depth":14},{"id":96,"text":"no matter how offensive .","depth":14},{"id":97,"text":"- Political maps .","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"In the second case","depth":15},{"id":99,"text":"to reach the court this year","depth":15},{"id":100,"text":"on political redistricting ,","depth":14},{"id":101,"text":"the justices must decide","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"whether nonpartisan commissions can replace state legislatures","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"in drawing congressional district maps every 10 years .","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"Those commissions are used in seven states ,","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"including California ,","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"to take the redistricting process out of the hands of politicians with a vested interest .","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"But the Arizona state Legislature 's Republican majority argued","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"that the Constitution gives that power solely to state legislatures .","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"A majority of the court 's justices appeared to agree during oral arguments .","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"- Religious signs .","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"Also from Arizona comes a case","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"combining religious freedom and highway clutter .","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"Tiny Good News Community Church is challenging the town of Gilbert 's sign ordinances ,","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"which restrict signs","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"advertising upcoming events","depth":15},{"id":116,"text":"- such as church services -","depth":15},{"id":117,"text":"far more than political and ideological signs .","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"While acknowledging","depth":14},{"id":119,"text":"that local governments can regulate for the purposes of beautification ,","depth":14},{"id":120,"text":"the justices likely will rule","depth":14},{"id":121,"text":"that the town went too far","depth":15},{"id":122,"text":"in limiting church event signs to 6 square feet and 13 hours .","depth":15},{"id":123,"text":"That would be good news for Good News .","depth":12}],"relations":[{"parent":247,"left":0,"right":246,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":246,"left":133,"right":245,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":133,"left":125,"right":132,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":125,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":128,"right":131,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":3,"right":127,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":127,"left":4,"right":126,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":126,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":131,"left":130,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":130,"left":7,"right":129,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":245,"left":149,"right":244,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":149,"left":11,"right":148,"relation":"organization","nuc